{
  "text": "Finally, the determinants of exchange rate depend crucially on the time horizon. [CITATION_1] examines the relative importance of macro vis-\u00e0-vis micro variables in determining the exchange rate movements over different time horizons with the help of primary information collected from the Indian foreign exchange dealers. The findings suggest that while speculation and central bank intervention are the major determinants of the intraday movements in the exchange rate, in the medium run and long run, economic fundamentals played a major role in determining the rate movement.",
